profile_positions.description:
- Contributed to the setup of the new HR organization for supporting business growth which grew from 80 to 125 employees over a 10 months period;
- Streamlined automatic HR processes, centralizing information, resulting in bottlenecks, error and loss of data removal, all while increasing transparency, communication across departments, and speed of processing;
- Designed, implemented and maintained HR & GA policies and procedures;
- Administered the onboarding of an average of 6 new hires per month by initiating the preonboarding process of equipment ordering, email account creation, managing employee benefits, preparing welcome gifts, offering the first day orientation and scheduling introduction meetings with VPs based on availability and number of hires;
- Administered the offboarding of employees by collecting all necessary offboarding data, suspending email accounts, cancelling and transferring employee benefits, equipment returns and purchasing, and arranging tailor-made farewell gifts;
- Remastered unused programs due to COVID (Exchange Program, Volunteer and Charity Program, Wellbeing Program) resulting in extra employee benefits and program cadence;
- Compiled and updated 125+ employee data, ensuring accuracy and validity of information;
- Assisted the finance team and external accounting firm with relevant tasks such as SEPA and manual payments, NL salary and wage payments, billing across countries, bookkeeping, bank reports and invoice tracking, resulting in a clear overview of company assets from 2018 to present day, accurate cost centers per item and on-time payments;
- Arranging company events and meaningful gifts to employees, clients and prospects within
close deadlines;
- Managed contract and price negotiations with vendors and service providers, focusing on finding the best service quality at a lower price;
- Supervising general office operations for all global offices.

-Assisted the HRM in the company’s biggest project of closing the B.V. by contacting
and receiving offers for office asset purchase, coordinating with the moving company, preparing shipments to Germany, emptying the office, drafting and sending out cancellation letters to providers, drafting settlement agreements and GDPR consent forms, adjusting and creating overviews of holiday balance, helping with outplacement for the employees who did not transfer to Germany by contacting RWC, UVW and recruitment agencies, holding presentations and offboarding personnel tasks;
- Managed expat affairs tasks such as assisting Japanese expatriates with relocation to Japan and Germany, visa extension and visa cancellation, IND appointments, deregistration from
local municipality, pension administration, housing arrangements (pre-check out and final
inspections, utilities cancellation, property cleaning), mail forwarding to current address;
- Supported the HRM in collecting information for the monthly (expat) payroll;
- Organized, compiled and kept the personnel files and records in electronic and paper form up-to-date, including processing employee sick leaves, holiday leaves, paternity and maternity leaves, etc., resulting in a easier data transfer cross-border;
- Drafted HR documents such as: employment contracts, addendums, testimonials, company belongings forms, salary and bonus letters, etc. and updating the organizational chart and phone list;
- Assisted HRM in projects and initiative, such as scheduling meetings, recording meeting minutes, updating the merger progress, creating and sharing documents cross-border;
- Managed all GA related activities such as supplier communication, mail distribution, purchasing and organizing office supplies and kitchen supplies, maintaining proper stock levels, collecting IT support tickets and follow to completion, arranging corporate events and gifts, company car fleet management, being first point of contact for the general reception.
